From 90c8c31e19d4fe659dc38e537f241e79266ff478 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Thorsten Blum <thorsten.blum@linux.dev>
Date: Mon, 30 Jun 2025 12:54:18 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] ALSA: timer: Replace deprecated strcpy() with strscpy()
Git-commit: 90c8c31e19d4fe659dc38e537f241e79266ff478
Patch-mainline: v6.17-rc1
References: jsc#PED-14430 jsc#PED-14297 jsc#PED-14024

strcpy() is deprecated; use strscpy() instead.

No functional changes intended.

Link: https://github.com/KSPP/linux/issues/88
Signed-off-by: Thorsten Blum <thorsten.blum@linux.dev>
Link: https://patch.msgid.link/20250630105420.1448-2-thorsten.blum@linux.dev
Signed-off-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

---
 sound/core/timer.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/sound/core/timer.c b/sound/core/timer.c
index 8072183c33d3..3ce12264eed8 100644
--- a/sound/core/timer.c
+++ b/sound/core/timer.c
@@ -1195,7 +1195,7 @@ static int snd_timer_register_system(void)
 	err = snd_timer_global_new("system", SNDRV_TIMER_GLOBAL_SYSTEM, &timer);
 	if (err < 0)
 		return err;
-	strcpy(timer->name, "system timer");
+	strscpy(timer->name, "system timer");
 	timer->hw = snd_timer_system;
 	priv = kzalloc(sizeof(*priv), GFP_KERNEL);
 	if (priv == NULL) {
